22 13-01.2-02. Standards for safeguarding customer information.
23 1. A financial corporation shall develop, implement, and maintain a comprehensive
24 information security program.
25 2. The information security program must:
26 a. Be written in one or more readily accessible parts; and
27 b. Maintain administrative, technical, and physical safeguards that are appropriate
28 to the financial corporation's size and complexity, the nature and scope of the
29 financial corporation's activities, and the sensitivity of any customer information at
30 issue.
31 3. The financial corporation shall develop a security program that:
