1 a. Ensures the security and confidentiality of customer information;
2 b. Protects against any anticipated threats or hazards to the security or integrity of
3 such information; and
4 c. Protects against unauthorized access to or use of such information that could
5 result in substantial harm or inconvenience to any customer.
6 13 - 01.2 - 03. Elements of a security program .
7 1. A financial corporation's information security program must denote a designation of a
8 qualified individual responsible for overseeing and implementing the financial
9 corporation's information security program and enforcing the financial corporation's
10 information security program. The qualified individual may be employed by the
11 financial corporation, an affiliate, or a service provider.
12 2. If a financial corporation designates an individual employed by an affiliate or service
13 provider as the qualified individual, the financial corporation shall:
14 a. Retain responsibility for compliance with this chapter;
15 b. Designate a senior member of the financial corporation's personnel to be
16 responsible for directing and overseeing the qualified individual; and
17 c. Require the service provider or affiliate to maintain an information security
18 program that protects the financial corporation in accordance with the
19 requirements of this chapter.
